        public static Iterator<Pixel> bresenham(Pixel start,
                                        Pixel end)
        Pixel iterator based on Bresenham's algorithm for a line between two discrete endpoints. The pixel returned by the iterator will always be the same object for efficiency; if you need to hold on to it, you should clone it first.
        Parameters:
        start - the coordinate of the start point
        end - the coordinate of the end point
        Returns:
        an iterator over the pixels in the line

      • bresenham

        public static Iterator<Pixel> bresenham(int x0,
                                        int y0,
                                        float fdx,
                                        float fdy)
        Pixel iterator based on Bresenham's algorithm for a line starting at a given point, with an angle given by the provided x and y deltas. The pixel returned by the iterator will always be the same object for efficiency; if you need to hold on to it, you should clone it first. Note: The returned iterator is infinite; that is it won't ever end.
        Parameters:
        x0 - the x-ordinate of the start point
        y0 - the y-ordinate of the start point
        fdx - the x-gradient
        fdy - the y-gradient
        Returns:
        an iterator over the pixels in the line

        Generate the pixels for the supercover of the line between two points. Based directly on code from Eugen Dedu.

        y1 - the y-ordinate of the start point
        x2 - the x-ordinate of the end point
        y2 - the y-ordinate of the end point
        Returns:
        the iterator of pixels representing the supercover line
        See Also:
